И масс-маркет, не будь дураком, тоже научился плести сумочки из кожи

hashtags: zara, parfois, nextdirect
caption:
Пару лет назад шумно выстрелили текстильные броши-цветы

Они были везде, на всём и на всех. Многие бренды выпускали рубашки, пиджаки, футболки с уже пришитыми огромными цветами. Объёмные цветы лепили себе на грудь стилисты, фэшн-инфлюенсеры, ведущие ток-шоу и офисные сотрудницы.

В общем, этих цветов было так много, что они порядком всем поднадоели‍♀️

Но от самого факта брошек модный мир не отказался, сейчас актуальны металлические или пластиковые броши небольших размеров. Но тренд не столько на сами брошки, сколько на стилистические игрища с ними. С помощью брошки можно интересно задрапировать свитер, подколоть шарфик или сделать имитацию необычной пуговицы на рубашке

Если хотите прикупить себе брошку с картинок - найти её в магазинах можно по ссылке в моём телеграм-канале в этом посте: https://t.me/styleinsidebudapest/187

#zara #parfois #nextdirect

hashtags: WeddingSinger, WeddingSeason, LakeDistrictBreak, MinimoonVibes, AmblesideAdventures, BabyShowerVibes, ProjectGarden, TrentBridge, BankHolidayWeddings, DunstonHallEstate, WoottonHallEstate, OwstonHallHotel, UKWeddings, NextFashion, ContentCreatorUK, EventSinger, WeddingContent, WeddingRoundUp, LifeLately, LoveWhatIDo, BrideAndGroom, WeddingInspo, WeddingVibes, WeddingWeekender, JustMarriedMoments
caption:
hello lovely people, 

Long time no speak ✨ it’s been a craaaazy couple of weeks so shall we do a round up? 

1. After the I Do awards, me & Tim went to the Lake District and stayed at @thelangdalehotel  highly recommend for a honeymoon/minimoon! 

2. We hired a boat on lake Windermere  

3. Wondered around Ambleside ‍♀️ 

4. Went to my lovely friends baby shower, I’m sorry but how gorgeous is she  

5. The cutest decor  

6. The bestest ✨

7. We started project garden  

8. Went to Trent Bridge to watch England vs Zimbabwe test  

9. Then began the mad bank holiday of weddings! Starting at @dunstonhallestate for N & S 

10.  The flowers - I’m obsessed! @touchofcharmvenuestylist you are incredible! 

11. This dress is giving odd muse but really it’s @nextofficial (next has me in a choke hold at the minute ) 

12. I then drove over to @thewoottonhallestate for C & D to celebrate their evening reception with them ✨

13. Rounding up with the final wedding of the weekend at @owstonhallhotel for J & D  a new venue for me and look at this ceremony room!

14. Tilt your head to see the best team ever! Nothing better than turning up to a wedding and getting to hang out with your supplier friends all day ☺️ @pearsphotography @icecapweddings @theaisleedit.uk @arabellabarnesbailey

hashtags: SustainableTextiles, UKManufacturing, NextFashion, BritishTextile
caption:
On 28 April, UKFT attended the NEXT@Fashion InStyle exhibition, organised by the Hong Kong Trade Development Council at the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Centre.

The show brought together designers, innovators and material specialists from around the world to explore the future of fashion through innovation and collaboration. 

The British Textile showcased the heritage techniques with forward-thinking approaches to meet the growing demand for sustainability, transparency and performance in global fashion supply chains.

#SustainableTextiles #UKManufacturing #NextFashion #BritishTextile

I found this super cute rainbow table at a NEXT outlet store! I’d only been talking about it 24hrs earlier, saying it was too expensive for me to buy full-price online (it’s still for sale at that price on their website), then just by chance I walked into the NEXT outlet store & saw it there for more than half price! caption:
Hi Bee,
 
Yes I would avoid any clothing for your little one that is not 100% cotton. Please note you do not need to cover your little ones feet for sleep you may use babygros with no feet from day one it is not a problem while sleeping it would only be a problem in cold weather during your little ones up time.
 
Babies do not need their feet covered to sleep the sleep bag and the wrap keeps their feet warm and it is a good thing for them to learn to sleep with their toes rubbing on the sleep bag which feel like adult sheets. This means when they are old enough to sleep without a sleep bag it feels normal on their toes and not foreign. This is one of the reasons all my sleep bags have the same inside layer of fabric to avoid problems when you no longer use the sleep bag. If you really would like feet you can get really big sizes from M&S or NEXT I found the M&S ones very big.
 
WARNING | The advice given by The International Baby Whisperer PTY LTD is only to be followed if you are using Save Our Sleep branded products and should not be followed when using any other branded products. When using any other brand of products please follow your countries health advice.

Ad|Pr invite 
  
.
.
.
We had the best time visiting @draytonmanorpark last week. Peyton and Oakley were able to go on almost all the rides in Thomas Land (Oaks is 96cm so missed out on a couple) the queuing system was great and we didn’t have to wait long at all to get on each ride. There was a great selection of food and drinks facilities located around the park too. 
.
.
We ventured over to the zoo area and went on the Dino trail which all the children loved. There was an outdoor play area and then we took the Thomas train ride back down to Thomas Land. There was so much to see and do it really was a fun filled day for all the family and would suit a whole range of ages. I was a bit worried about being a single parent with two little ones incase I couldn’t take them both on with me but for the majority of the rides in Thomas Land they could both ride with me at the same time (with the exception of the rides that required the rider to be over 1m) 
.
.
.

hashtags: Payyourworkers, RespectLabourRights, Next, NextOutfit, NextHaul, OOTD, FashionBlooger, UkFashion, FastFashion, PovertWages, GarmentWorkersNeedUnions, HumanRightsCampaign, WageTheft, EndWageTheft, LabourRightsAreHumanRights, NextFashion, UkFashionBlogger, UkFashionBloggers, ShareYourProfits, 10CentsMore
caption:
Next say they take their responsibility towards supply chain workers seriously and that they joined the ILO Call to Action to make sure their workers are paid. 

But the Call to Action has no conditions ensuring funds distributed to suppliers pay workers’ wages let alone FULL wages. There are also no consequences for signatory brands if workers in their supply chain do not receive income support.

Workers around the world have been protesting because the solutions brands are committing to are not enough. 

We want Next to set an example for the industry.

Take the NEXT step: #Payyourworkers & #RespectLabourRights

Link to info in bio
.
.
.
$NXT.L #Next #NextOutfit #NextHaul #OOTD #FashionBlooger #UkFashion #FastFashion #PovertWages #GarmentWorkersNeedUnions #HumanRightsCampaign #RespectLabourRights #WageTheft #EndWageTheft #LabourRightsAreHumanRights #NextFashion #UkFashionBlogger #UkFashionBloggers #ShareYourProfits #10CentsMore

hashtags: PayYourWorkers., RespectLabourRights, Next, NextOutfit, NextHaul, OOTD, FashionBlooger, UkFashion, FastFashion, PovertWages, GarmentWorkersNeedUnions, HumanRightsCampaign, WageTheft, EndWageTheft, LabourRightsAreHumanRights, NextFashion, UkFashionBlogger, UkFashionBloggers, ShareYourProfits, 10CentsMore
caption:
Today @nextofficial meets for their annual shareholder meeting and we’re calling on them to set an example for the industry & #PayYourWorkers. 

Brands have underpaid the workers who make their clothes for decades, leaving garment workers the least able to pay the price for the pandemic, while brands have kept their profits. Garment workers are owed as much as $5.8 billion in unpaid wages from the first 3 months of the pandemic alone. 

We call on Next & other major brands to 1) ensure the garment workers in their supply chain receive their full wages during the pandemic and severance if they lose their jobs, and 2) #RespectLabourRights by protecting workers’ right to organise and bargain collectively. 

Don't wait for the NEXT crisis: Take the NEXT step.

Info on our pay your workers campaign in the bio
.
.
.

caption:
Next Fashion Designer of Tokyo受賞
Next Fashion Designer of Tokyoの最終審査の結果、
エスモード・東京校の2025年卒業生の二宮櫻壽さんが東京都知事賞フリー部門の大賞を受賞しました
また、同じく卒業生の濱夏歩さんが東京都知事賞フリー部門の特別選抜賞を受賞しました。
おめでとう

Winners of the Next Fashion Designer of Tokyo
As a result of the final judging of the Next Fashion Designer of Tokyo competition, Ouju Ninomiya, an ESMOD TOKYO 2025 graduate student, won the Grand Prize in Free Design Category of the Tokyo Governor’s Award. Another graduate student, Natsuho Hama, won the special selection Award in the Free Design Category. 
Congratulations to both of them

caption:
When you find a bathroom that matches your outfit 

Had such a lovely time last weekend soaking up the sunshine with the loveliest group! 

The weather has been sooo dreamy lately and it’s supposed to be sticking around this weekend too. 

Can highly recommend these gorgeous floaty mini dresses from @nextofficial @nextofficialpr for your next girls’ brunch (different prints available). They’re loose, comfy and juuust the right amount of short (even on my tall body)!

Knee-high boots are @veryuk !

Hope you’re all having an amazing week.

caption:
那是一天第一次參加大型兒童戶外活動的OOTD

在闖關的時候，第二關玩顏料褲子跟鞋子已經差不多毀了，心想反正我還有兩套衣服換然後回家可以趕快洗或泡水一下

hashtags: pfw, rickowensdrkshdw, mannequinhomme, lestyleavanttout, largentnachètepaslebonheur, visionetattitude, nextfashion, pfw25, nextfaceoffashion, futureoffashion
caption: @rickowensonline Un cowboy du futur, une silhouette qui défie le temps et les tendances. Ici, la mode ne suit pas les règles, elle les crée. Mélange d’héritage africain et de modernité brute, ce look est une déclaration : l’avenir appartient à ceux qui osent Les marques qui recherchent l’audace, les agences en quête de visages qui marquent l’histoire, prenez note. Le futur du style est déjà en marche. Le style ne s’achète pas, il se vit.  Ce n’est pas une question d’argent ou de célébrité, mais de vision, d’attitude et de goût. Savoir qui tu es, ce qui te met en valeur, et comment marier les couleurs, c’est ça le vrai luxe Les grandes marques et agences recherchent plus qu’un visage : elles cherchent une identité forte, une présence qui marque les esprits. Et si le futur de la mode, c’était moi ?  #pfw #rickowensdrkshdw #mannequinhomme #lestyleavanttout #largentnachètepaslebonheur #visionetattitude #nextfashion con  #pfw25 #rickowensdrkshdw #nextfaceoffashion #mannequinhomme #futureoffashion

hashtags: sundaymood☀️, citybreak, lisbon, traveller, sightseeing, linen, linenshirt, widelegtrousers, mymarks, hmxme, nextofficial, mystyle
caption:
#sundaymood☀️ - all things floaty for a city break

This weekend my partner and I met up with some close work colleagues in Lisbon. 
We are already fans of Portugal and this city did not disappoint.  Bustling, beautiful and full of history- it was lovely. If you haven’t done already- check out my stories as to why I loved my visit. I will also save this as a highlight for anyone else for inspo. 

I opted for a floaty pair of current @nextofficial trousers (which are super light) with a butter yellow @hm Premium shirt. The trainers were necessary as we covered a lot of Lisbon. 
Hope you e had a fab weekend x.

hashtags: 2y6m20d, 買鞋真係天性嚟, 首先要買多個鞋櫃, littlegirl, happyshoppingday, 兩歲半人仔買鞋記, toddlerlife, lifeinuk, nextdirect, kidsshoes, 閃燈波鞋出沒注意, 阿里日常, 成長記録, ArianaY, 幸福小人類
caption:
買鞋記

Ari講咗好耐想買對好女仔款，一定要襯裙至好睇嗰啲婆仔鞋 好幾次行街經過都話要買要買，阿媽梗係當耳邊風聽住先

唔知係咪因為阿媽平時揀開都係運動款多(易襯嘛)，Ari一見到啲唔係運動款嘅鞋就引起咗「想要」嘅意欲

今日專登出嚟買Ari心目中嘅公.主.鞋 試完一對又一對，果然係貪新鮮的小孩‍ 最後竟然比佢發現一對驚世閃燈波鞋‼️ 講明只可以買一對鞋，再三確認之下，Ari都係逃唔出閃閃燈嘅誘惑 其餘嘅就留返出年先買啦

23Nov23 #2y6m20d

caption: NEXT HOME-WEAR HAUL  Next I feel, can often get overlooked as a place for home wear, especially as they can be on the pricier side. However these  have added the finishing staging touches to my home, and add that “wow” factor!  Item 1) OX set this was £22 and is fully usable! My nephew loves playing this when he comes round and I just love how quirky it is. 2) diamanté crystal wall art the quality and detail of this piece is just amazing, it was £45 and is the perfect size for any smaller areas you want to make pop. Some of the gems are textured which makes the room pop when the sun hits. 3) leopard reed diffuser £12, a modern twist on a needed household item...bought to match item number 4) Diamanté panther £45 (see previous post for more detail) finally item number 5) “Get Naked” sign, just £12 !! Wall art choices in a bathroom can be tricky, both for practicality and style. My personal advice would be to stick with three main styles “quotes, landscapes/ nature and florals” when it comes to bathrooms. I went with the quote as it adds humour and makes an impact. Side note ... meet my kitty Coco , she says hi!  ✨ #next #nextinterior #nexthomeware #nexthomefinds #nexthaul #shoppinghaul #homewearhaul #designer #designinspo #designinspiration #designinterior #designing #feature #style #home #lotd #pictures #cats #catsofinatagram #follow #fashion #interiorfashion #modernhome #finishingtouches #homesweethome  #homestyledecor @nextofficial

caption:
There’s a new episode of #thelongandtheshortofit up on my stories now! Featuring gorgeous plus size blogger @lucy_earnshaw and of course my insta wife, and long one to my short one @wearitlikeruth .
.
.
.
We’ve loved welcoming guest stars to help us out with #thelongandtheshortofit ❤️. Whilst it was fun to show how clothes looked on Ruth and I with our different heights, we also appreciate that women come in all sorts of shapes and sizes, and felt it was important to reflect that in the series.  Lucy is our third guest, and she was able to give a plus size perspective on high street shopping, which really opened our eyes to some of the difficulties faced by women size 18+. .
.
.
A lot of high street stores will only have these sizes online, but @nextofficial were brilliant for us, as we were able to try on a size 6, 10 and 20 in most items.
.
.
.
It was lovely catching up with Lucy. She’s a top girl and we’re so grateful to her for helping us out this time! Give her a follow, she has brilliant style .
.
.
Head on over to my stories now for a look, and tell us what you’d like to see from #thelongandtheshortofit in future episodes! We’d love to hear from you and know what you’d find useful .
.
.
.
All three outfits @nextofficial .
❤️ALSO, IT’S #sharethestylesaturday TIME! PLEASE JOIN IN AND TAG MYSELF AND @oliviajessloves ❤️
.
.
.

caption:
First day of #octoberhalfterm and we headed over to our local stately home @harewoodhouse to let off some steam 
.
I decided to wear head to toe knitwear which was a good decision as it’s pretty nippy today but it took me about 45 mins to de-bobble everything first as otherwise I looked like a fuzzy vagrant...
.
Anyway I was pretty cosy and spent a good 4 hours kicking leaves, squawking at birds and making wands out of sticks and strings for my little witches ‍♀️ ‍♀️
.
Scarlett took these pics and tbh she was pretty bossy with her directions...
.
#ootd details are - leggings @primark (old) but they do a variation of them every year, star jumper @nextofficial, cardigan I bought in a boutique #adeje in Tenerife and boots are this season @primark  .
.
.
.
.
.

caption: E L L A▪️ Back to School for @nextofficial ✏️ with her friend @emily_performs2017 genuine fun  @bruceandbrown #nextofficial #nextofficialkids #schooluniform #bruceandbrown

I’ve had a lot of new followers lately and some questions around my hysterectomy so hopefully this post helps.

I don’t know who needs to hear this but I PROMISE you that you are stronger than you think

If you have to start again…. You can do so and come back even stronger

If you’re feeling low you can get your spark back

You hold the ability to take action

Action builds motivation which then gives you the momentum to keep going…. Small steps done consistently make the biggest difference

With a personalised approach to nutrition, movement and other tweaks you can absolutely transform how you’re feeling. You don’t have to make drastic changes - small tweaks to what you’re doing make the biggest difference.

And one last thing always remember progress and not perfection 

ps - so many typo and grammar errors on this post so apologies for that but I’m not redoing it

In the middle of nowhere … 
 
Just 4 sisters, we ate, drank, danced, laughed, played cards and games (I won catchphrase) and watched  tv (Rivals and Bump, both brilliant). We watched the fireworks and had a dip in the hot tub. Pj’s days and no make-up. The perfect weekend.

hashtags: lifeatnext, nextembassador, next, nextfashion
caption:
Hello
A little introduction about me…. 

My name is Molly and I am now an official ‘Em’bassador’ for @lifeatnext @nextofficial ✨

I graduated University in 2024 with a BA (Hons) degree in Textile design! I am a specialist in knit and digital print.
My journey with @nextofficial started when I was in my second year at University. I had the opportunity to design a menswear S/S collection to win a placement at Next HQ, which I won! My collection was called ‘Wild West’ which was a collection combining knitwear and print design. 
In the summer of 2023, I completed my placement and had the most amazing time ever! This then led me to my next opportunity… Experiencing more placement in the womenswear print department in 2024! Having these opportunities made me extremely passionate about Next as a brand and I craved more!!

During the Christmas period in 2024, I applied for a retail job at Next. This is where I currently am with my career, and I’m enjoying experiencing all areas of Next! I now work with the most amazing team at 349!

I’m excited to get started as an official ‘Em’bassador’ for Next, and I can’t wait to bring you all along on my journey!✨ 

#lifeatnext#nextembassador#next#nextfashion

"bills to be paid!!!!" and all that jazz  I just love their stuff and how well they wash! T-Shirts 2 for €13, Dress €11.50, Leggings (2 pair) €11.60, Blouse €17.50. 
To be fair, for the first 5 months of her life I don't think I had to buy anything for her other than vests as her wardrobe was supplied by all her generous family and friends... so this is allowed  (keep justifying yourself there Jess ) #nextkidswear #nextkids #nexthaul #shopping #babygirl #babygirlsclothes #babyootd #babystyle #babyfashionista #babyfashion #kidsfashion #kidsclothes #kidsclothing #stylishbaby #style #instamama #instablog #mumblogger #mumlife

caption:
Bonjour from the beautiful French Riviera where we are celebrating my beautiful mum’s birthday 

Whether you’re exploring the charming streets of Nice or soaking up the sun on the Côte d’Azur, I’ve found the perfect multi-tasking outfit. 

This vibrant 2-piece linen blend co-ord set from @nextofficial is an absolute game-changer! The lightweight fabric kept me cool while the colorful design makes sure you stand out in all the right ways. 

I wore mine over my swimwear for a seamless transition from sightseeing to the beach, and then to a nearby seaside bar for sunset cocktails. 

No need to pack multiple outfits when one set does it all! 

Versatile, comfy, and effortlessly chic—what more could you ask for?  

#FrenchRiviera #SummerStyle #TravelEssentials #NextFashion #ChicAndComfy #ghstyle
#NextWomens 

Search for “Blue Palm Print” to shop the look  #ThankMeLater

We stayed in this beautiful hotel which had endless sea views from the balcony. I found a great deal on Expedia; I’ve popped the link in my bio for you

caption:
I’ve worn these trousers on repeat this weekend. They are super comfy and very bloat friendly. I wore them out to eat twice and they didn’t hurt my tummy at all. 

Both the trousers and this bag were bought with my Christmas vouchers in the January sale. ☺️

I’ve been on the lookout for a burgundy bag that’s a bit larger than my usual crossbody style. This one is lovely and it would be perfect if it had gold metal details instead of silver but I can put up with that! It has 2 straps, this short one and a longer one that you can wear on your shoulder.

️EMMA: buna andu! mergi in aceeasi zona si crezi ca te descurci bine la tinute? tinute de azi e mult prea simpla, mai ales alegerile accesoriilor… pantofii sunt foarte nepotriviti si urati, geanta trebuia sa fie de o nuanță de rosu mai inchisa, caciula e total din alt film si blana e doar de umplutură. accesoriile intr adevar, sunt okish ca sunt finute si merg cu rochia, dat sunt foarte urate ele in sine, forma lor. coafura nu mi se pare ca merge. machiajul e ok, unghiile sunt urate. efectul asta e urat nu l mai pune ca strici estetica tinutei. nota 1️⃣

️DAVID: Buna Andu! Piesa principala e urata, caciula e duce in zona de personaj si arata urat, machiajul oribil, pantofii nu merg, geanta ieftina, coafura nu mi place. Nota 1!

ERIKA: Bună andu! Bafaje de joc mi se pare ca ai același ținute în fiecare zi ,toate vechi și urâte, geanta e foarte urata, la makeup as fi pus altceva nu se potrivesc nuanțele, căciula nu merge,pantofii nu mi se pare ca merg cu rochia , da pe scrut nu mi place nimic 1️⃣!

LAVINIA: Bună Andu! Piesa principală e ok cat de cat, caciula nu trebuia sa o pui ca e oribila și nu se potrivește, geanta e oribila la fel și machiajul iar accesoriile sunt foarte urate. Nota 1!

caption:
Skirt love. 
I saw this skirt on @emmateacherstyle ‘s account a couple of weeks ago and loved it. So I waited until payday and then treated myself. 
As soon as I saw it I knew it was just what I’d been looking for. Black, the right length, elasticated waist and it even has pockets for bonus points! 

This was a perfect outfit for walking round London this weekend. If it had been colder I’d have worn secret leggings underneath but it was pretty warm on Saturday. I had a biker jacket too which was in my husband’s rucksack at this point. We walked all round London in the sunshine and it was fantastic. 

Skirt - @nextofficial @nextofficialpr 
Bag - Tarelle (AD)
